1. to exceed; to overtake; to surpass; to transcend; to pass; to cross; ultra-; super-
2. to make a copy; to plagiarize; to search and seize; to raid; to grab; to go off with; to take a shortcut; to make a turning move; to fold one's arms
3. money; paper money
4. to grab; to snatch up
5. to plagiarize
6. unbent bow
7. (literary) sad; sorrowful; disappointed; frustrated
8. to blanch; to parboil
9. clamor; uproar; annoyance

1. to worry about
2. chip (in gambling); token (for counting); ticket
3. to prepare; to plan; to raise (funds)
4. resource; way; means
5. hatred; animosity; enmity; foe; enemy; to feel animosity toward (the wealthy, foreigners etc)
6. to entertain; to repay; to return; to reward; to compensate; to reply; to answer
7. dense; crowded; thick; many
8. (light) silk; CL: pǐ
9. comrades; friends; companions
10. (archaic) used in ladies' names
11. canopy; curtain
12. forlorn; vexed; disappointed
13. species of tree resistant to cold weather
14. salience; prominent; notable
15. arable fields; cultivated field; class; category
16. silk
17. bed curtain; coverlet
18. to collate; to proofread
19. Leuciscus macropus
